dot11ShortSlotTimeOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the Short Slot Time option as defined in 7.3.1.4 is implemented. The default value of this attribute is false.

dot11ShortSlotTimeOptionEnabled.name: dot11ShortSlotTimeOptionEnabled
dot11ShortSlotTimeOptionEnabled.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the Short Slot Time option as defined in 7.3.1.4 is enabled. The default value of this attribute is false.

dot11PhyHTTable.name: dot11PhyHTTable
dot11PhyHTTable.description: Entry of attributes for dot11PhyHTTable. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyHTEntry.name: dot11PhyHTEntry
dot11PhyHTEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyHTEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11FortyMHzOperationImplemented.name: dot11FortyMHzOperationImplemented
dot11FortyMHzOperationImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the 40 MHz Operation is implemented. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11FortyMHzOperationEnabled.name: dot11FortyMHzOperationEnabled
dot11FortyMHzOperationEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the 40 MHz Operation is enabled. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11CurrentPrimaryChannel.name: dot11CurrentPrimaryChannel
dot11CurrentPrimaryChannel.description: This attribute indicates the operating channel. If 20/40 MHz Mode is currently in use then this attribute indicates the primary channel.

dot11CurrentSecondaryChannel.name: dot11CurrentSecondaryChannel
dot11CurrentSecondaryChannel.description: This attribute indicates the channel number of the secondary channel. If 20/40 MHz mode is not currently in use, this attribute value shall be 0.

dot11NumberOfSpatialStreamsImplemented.name: dot11NumberOfSpatialStreamsImplemented
dot11NumberOfSpatialStreamsImplemented.description: This attribute indicates the maximum number of spatial streams implemented. The default value of this attribute is 2.

dot11NumberOfSpatialStreamsEnabled.name: dot11NumberOfSpatialStreamsEnabled
dot11NumberOfSpatialStreamsEnabled.description: This attribute indicates the maximum number of spatial streams enabled. The default value of this attribute is 2.

dot11GreenfieldOptionImplemented.name: dot11GreenfieldOptionImplemented
dot11GreenfieldOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the HT Greenfield option is implemented. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11GreenfieldOptionEnabled.name: dot11GreenfieldOptionEnabled
dot11GreenfieldOptionEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the HT Greenfield option is enabled. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ShortGIOptionInTwentyImplemented.name: dot11ShortGIOptionInTwentyImplemented
dot11ShortGIOptionInTwentyImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Short Guard option is implemented for 20 MHz operation. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ShortGIOptionInTwentyEnabled.name: dot11ShortGIOptionInTwentyEnabled
dot11ShortGIOptionInTwentyEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Short Guard option is enabled for 20 MHz operation. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ShortGIOptionInFortyImplemented.name: dot11ShortGIOptionInFortyImplemented
dot11ShortGIOptionInFortyImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Short Guard option is implemented for 40 MHz operation. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ShortGIOptionInFortyEnabled.name: dot11ShortGIOptionInFortyEnabled
dot11ShortGIOptionInFortyEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Short Guard option is enabled for 40 MHz operation. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11LDPCCodingOptionImplemented.name: dot11LDPCCodingOptionImplemented
dot11LDPCCodingOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the LDPC coding option is implemented. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11LDPCCodingOptionEnabled.name: dot11LDPCCodingOptionEnabled
dot11LDPCCodingOptionEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the LDPC coding option is enabled. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11TxSTBCOptionImplemented.name: dot11TxSTBCOptionImplemented
dot11TxSTBCOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the entity is capable of transmitting frames using Space-Time Block Code (STBC) option. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11TxSTBCOptionEnabled.name: dot11TxSTBCOptionEnabled
dot11TxSTBCOptionEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the entity's capability of transmitting frames using Space-Time Block Code (STBC) option is enabled. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11RxSTBCOptionImplemented.name: dot11RxSTBCOptionImplemented
dot11RxSTBCOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the entity is capable of receiving frames that are sent using the Space-Time Block Code (STBC). The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11RxSTBCOptionEnabled.name: dot11RxSTBCOptionEnabled
dot11RxSTBCOptionEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the entity's capability of receiving frames that are sent using the Space-Time Block Code (STBC) is enabled. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11BeamFormingOptionImplemented.name: dot11BeamFormingOptionImplemented
dot11BeamFormingOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Beam Forming option is implemented. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11BeamFormingOptionEnabled.name: dot11BeamFormingOptionEnabled
dot11BeamFormingOptionEnabled.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Beam Forming option is enabled. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11HighestSupportedDataRate.name: dot11HighestSupportedDataRate
dot11HighestSupportedDataRate.description: This attribute shall specify the Highest Data Rate in Mb/s at which the station may receive data. The default value of this attribute shall be 0.

dot11TxMCSSetDefined.name: dot11TxMCSSetDefined
dot11TxMCSSetDefined.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the Tx MCS set is defined. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11TxRxMCSSetNotEqual.name: dot11TxRxMCSSetNotEqual
dot11TxRxMCSSetNotEqual.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the supported Tx and Rx MCS sets are not equal. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11TxMaximumNumberSpatialStreamsSuppor.name: dot11TxMaximumNumberSpatialStreamsSupported
dot11TxMaximumNumberSpatialStreamsSuppor.description: This attribute indicates the Tx maximum number of spatial streams supported. The default value of this attribute is 0.

dot11TxUnequalModulationSupported.name: dot11TxUnequalModulationSupported
dot11TxUnequalModulationSupported.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that Tx unequal modulation is supported. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11SupportedMCSTxTable.name: dot11SupportedMCSTxTable
dot11SupportedMCSTxTable.description: The Transmit MCS supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from 1 to 127, subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedMCSTxEntry.name: dot11SupportedMCSTxEntry
dot11SupportedMCSTxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the dot11SupportedMCSTx Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11SupportedMCSTxIndex.name: dot11SupportedMCSTxIndex
dot11SupportedMCSTxIndex.description: Index object that identifies which MCS to access. Range is 1..255.

dot11SupportedMCSTxValue.name: dot11SupportedMCSTxValue
dot11SupportedMCSTxValue.description: The Transmit MCS supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from 1 to 127, subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedMCSRxTable.name: dot11SupportedMCSRxTable
dot11SupportedMCSRxTable.description: The receive MCS supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from 1 to 127, subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedMCSRxEntry.name: dot11SupportedMCSRxEntry
dot11SupportedMCSRxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the dot11SupportedMCSRx Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11SupportedMCSRxIndex.name: dot11SupportedMCSRxIndex
dot11SupportedMCSRxIndex.description: Index object that identifies which MCS to access. Range is 1..255.

dot11SupportedMCSRxValue.name: dot11SupportedMCSRxValue
dot11SupportedMCSRxValue.description: The receive MCS supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from 1 to 127, subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11TxBFConfigTable.name: dot11TxBFConfigTable
dot11TxBFConfigTable.description: Entry of attributes for dot11TxBFConfigTable. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11TxBFConfigEntry.name: dot11TxBFConfigEntry
dot11TxBFConfigEntry.description: An entry in the dot11TxBFConfig Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11ReceiveStaggerSoundingOptionImpleme.name: dot11ReceiveStaggerSoundingOptionImplemented
dot11ReceiveStaggerSoundingOptionImpleme.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the STA implementation supports the receiving of staggered sounding frames. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11TransmitStaggerSoundingOptionImplem.name: dot11TransmitStaggerSoundingOptionImplemented
dot11TransmitStaggerSoundingOptionImplem.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the STA implementation supports the transmission of staggered sounding frames. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ReceiveNDPOptionImplemented.name: dot11ReceiveNDPOptionImplemented
dot11ReceiveNDPOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the STA implementation is capable of receiving NDP as sounding frames. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11TransmitNDPOptionImplemented.name: dot11TransmitNDPOptionImplemented
dot11TransmitNDPOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that the STA implementation is capable of transmitting NDP as sounding frames. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ImplicitTxBFOptionImplemented.name: dot11ImplicitTxBFOptionImplemented
dot11ImplicitTxBFOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that STA implementation is capable of applying implicit transmit beamforming. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11CalibrationOptionImplemented.name: dot11CalibrationOptionImplemented
dot11CalibrationOptionImplemented.description: This attribute indicates the level of calibration supported by the STA implementation. The default value of this attribute is 0.

dot11ExplicitCSITxBFOptionImplemented.name: dot11ExplicitCSITxBFOptionImplemented
dot11ExplicitCSITxBFOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that STA implementation is capable of applying transmit beamforming using CSI explicit feedback in its transmission. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ExplicitNonCompressedbeamformingMat.name: dot11ExplicitNonCompressedbeamformingMatrixOptionImplemented
dot11ExplicitNonCompressedbeamformingMat.description: This attribute, when TRUE, indicates that STA implementation is capable of applying transmit beamforming using non-compressed beamforming matrix explicit feedback in its transmission. The default value of this attribute is FALSE.

dot11ExplicitBFCSIFeedbackOptionImplemen.name: dot11ExplicitBFCSIFeedbackOptionImplemented
dot11ExplicitBFCSIFeedbackOptionImplemen.description: This attribute indicates the level of CSI explicit feedback returned by the STA implementation. The default value of this attribute is 0.

dot11ExplicitNonCompressedbeamformingMat.name: dot11ExplicitNonCompressedbeamformingMatrixFeedbackOptionImplemented
dot11ExplicitNonCompressedbeamformingMat.description: This attribute indicates the level of non-compressed beamforming matrix explicit feedback returned by the STA implementation. The default value of this attribute is 0.

dot11ExplicitCompressedbeamformingMatrix.name: dot11ExplicitCompressedbeamformingMatrixFeedbackOptionImplemented
dot11ExplicitCompressedbeamformingMatrix.description: This attribute indicates the level of non-compressed beamforming matrix explicit feedback returned by the STA implementation. The default value of this attribute is 0.

dot11NumberBeamFormingCSISupportAntenna.name: dot11NumberBeamFormingCSISupportAntenna
dot11NumberBeamFormingCSISupportAntenna.description: This attribute indicates the maximum number of beamform antennas the beamformee can support when CSI feedback is required.

dot11NumberNonCompressedbeamformingMatri.name: dot11NumberNonCompressedbeamformingMatrixSupportAntenna
dot11NumberNonCompressedbeamformingMatri.description: This attribute indicates the maximum number of beamform antennas the beamformee can support when non-compressed beamforming matrix feedback is required.

dot11NumberCompressedbeamformingMatrixSu.name: dot11NumberCompressedbeamformingMatrixSupportAntenna
dot11NumberCompressedbeamformingMatrixSu.description: This attribute indicates the maximum number of beamform antennas the beamformee can support when compressed beamforming matrix feedback is required.

dot11MaxCSIFeedbackDelay.name: dot11MaxCSIFeedbackDelay
dot11MaxCSIFeedbackDelay.description: This attribute indicates the maximum allowed delay in microseconds between the transmission time of a sounding packet and the time a feedback response arrives (9.17.3 (Explicit feedback beamforming))

dot11PhyDSSSTable.name: dot11PhyDSSSTable
dot11PhyDSSSTable.description: Entry of attributes for dot11PhyDSSSEntry. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyDSSSEntry.name: dot11PhyDSSSEntry
dot11PhyDSSSEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyDSSSEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CurrentChannel.name: dot11CurrentChannel
dot11CurrentChannel.description: The current operating frequency channel of the DSSS PHY. Valid channel numbers are as defined in 15.4.6.2

dot11CCAModeSupported.name: dot11CCAModeSupported
dot11CCAModeSupported.description: dot11CCAModeSupported is a bit-significant value, representing all of the CCA modes supported by the PHY. Valid values are: energy detect only (ED-ONLY) = 01, carrier sense only (CS-ONLY) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (ED-and-CS)= 04 or the logical sum of any of these values. This attribute shall not be used to indicate the CCA modes supported by a higher rate extension PHY. Rather, the dot11HRCCAModeSupported attribute shall be used to indicate the CCA modes of the higher rate extension PHY.

dot11CurrentCCAMode.name: dot11CurrentCCAMode
dot11CurrentCCAMode.description: The current CCA method in operation. Valid values are: energy detect only (edonly) = 01, carrier sense only (csonly) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (edandcs)= 04. carrier sense with timer (cswithtimer)= 08 high rate carrier sense and energy detect (hrcsanded)= 16

dot11EDThreshold.name: dot11EDThreshold
dot11EDThreshold.description: The current Energy Detect Threshold being used by the DSSS PHY.

dot11PhyIRTable.name: dot11PhyIRTable
dot11PhyIRTable.description: Group of attributes for dot11PhyIRTable. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyIREntry.name: dot11PhyIREntry
dot11PhyIREntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyIR Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMax.name: dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMax
dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMax.description: This parameter, together with CCAWatchdogCountMax, determines when energy detected in the channel can be ignored.

dot11CCAWatchdogCountMax.name: dot11CCAWatchdogCountMax
dot11CCAWatchdogCountMax.description: This parameter, together with CCAWatchdogTimerMax, determines when energy detected in the channel can be ignored.

dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMin.name: dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMin
dot11CCAWatchdogTimerMin.description: The minimum value to which CCAWatchdogTimerMax can be set.

dot11CCAWatchdogCountMin.name: dot11CCAWatchdogCountMin
dot11CCAWatchdogCountMin.description: The minimum value to which CCAWatchdogCount can be set.

dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable
dot11RegDomainsSupportedTable.description: There are different operational requirements dependent on the regulatory domain. This attribute list describes the regulatory domains the PLCP and PMD support in this implementation. Currently defined values and their corresponding Regulatory Domains are: FCC (USA) = X'10', DOC (Canada) = X'20', ETSI (most of Europe) = X'30', Spain = X'31', France = X'32', MKK (Japan) = X'40', Other=X'00'

dot11RegDomainsSupportEntry.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportEntry
dot11RegDomainsSupportEntry.description: An entry in the dot11RegDomainsSupport Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11RegDomainsSupportIndex.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportIndex
dot11RegDomainsSupportIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used to identify instances of the columnar objects in the RegDomainsSupport Table.

dot11RegDomainsSupportValue.name: dot11RegDomainsSupportValue
dot11RegDomainsSupportValue.description: There are different operational requirements dependent on the regulatory domain. This attribute list describes the regulatory domains the PLCP and PMD support in this implementation. Currently de- fined values and their corresponding Regulatory Domains are: FCC (USA) = X'10', DOC (Canada) = X'20', ETSI (most of Europe) = X'30', Spain = X'31', France = X'32', MKK (Japan) = X'40'

dot11AntennasListTable.name: dot11AntennasListTable
dot11AntennasListTable.description: This table represents the list of antennae. An antenna can be marked to be capable of transmitting, receiving, and/or for participation in receive diversity. Each entry in this table represents a single antenna with its properties. The maximum number of antennae that can be contained in this table is 255.

dot11AntennasListEntry.name: dot11AntennasListEntry
dot11AntennasListEntry.description: An entry in the dot11AntennasListTable, representing the properties of a single antenna. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11AntennaListIndex.name: dot11AntennaListIndex
dot11AntennaListIndex.description: The unique index of an antenna which is used to identify the columnar objects in the dot11AntennasList Table.

dot11SupportedTxAntenna.name: dot11SupportedTxAntenna
dot11SupportedTxAntenna.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by dot11AntennaIndex can be used as a transmit antenna.

dot11SupportedRxAntenna.name: dot11SupportedRxAntenna
dot11SupportedRxAntenna.description: When true, this object indocates that the antenna represented by the dot11AntennaIndex xan be used as a receive antenna.

dot11DiversitySelectionRx.name: dot11DiversitySelectionRx
dot11DiversitySelectionRx.description: When true, this object indicates that the antenna represented by dot11AntennaIndex can be used for receive diversity. This object may only be true if the antenna can be used as a receive antenna, as indicated by dot11SupportedRxAntenna.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxTable.description: The Transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'02-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the dot11SupportedDataRatesTx Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access. Range is 1..255.

dot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue
dot11SupportedDataRatesTxValue.description: The Transmit bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'02-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s subject to limitations of each individual PHY.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxTable.description: The receive bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'002-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxEntry.description: An Entry (conceptual row) in the dot11SupportedDataRatesRx Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxIndex.description: Index object which identifies which data rate to access. Range is 1..255.

dot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue.name: dot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue
dot11SupportedDataRatesRxValue.description: The receive bit rates supported by the PLCP and PMD, represented by a count from X'02-X'7f, corresponding to data rates in increments of 500Kb/s from 1 Mb/s to 63.5 Mb/s.

dot11PhyOFDMTable.name: dot11PhyOFDMTable
dot11PhyOFDMTable.description: Group of attributes for dot11PhyOFDMTable. Implemented as a table indexed on ifindex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyOFDMEntry.name: dot11PhyOFDMEntry
dot11PhyOFDMEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyOFDM Table. ifIndex - Each IEEE 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11CurrentFrequency.name: dot11CurrentFrequency
dot11CurrentFrequency.description: The number of the current operating frequency channel of the OFDM PHY.

dot11TIThreshold.name: dot11TIThreshold
dot11TIThreshold.description: The Threshold being used to detect a busy medium (frequency). CCA shall report a busy medium upon detecting the RSSI above this threshold.

dot11FrequencyBandsSupported.name: dot11FrequencyBandsSupported
dot11FrequencyBandsSupported.description: The capability of the OFDM PHY implementation to operate in the three U-NII bands. Coded as an integer value of a three bit field as follows: bit 0 .. capable of operating in the lower (5.15-5.25 GHz) U-NII band bit 1 .. capable of operating in the middle (5.25-5.35 GHz) U-NII band bit 2 .. capable of operating in the upper (5.725-5.825 GHz) U-NII band For example, for an implementation capable of operating in the lower and mid bands this attribute would take the value 3.

dot11PhyHRDSSSTable.name: dot11PhyHRDSSSTable
dot11PhyHRDSSSTable.description: Entry of attributes for dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry. Implemented as a table indexed on ifIndex to allow for multiple instances on an Agent.

dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry.name: dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry
dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry.description: An entry in the dot11PhyHRDSSSEntry Table. ifIndex - Each 802.11 interface is represented by an ifEntry. Interface tables in this MIB module are indexed by ifIndex.

dot11ChannelAgilityPresent.name: dot11ChannelAgilityPresent
dot11ChannelAgilityPresent.description: This attribute indicates that the PHY is capable of channel agility.

dot11ChannelAgilityEnabled.name: dot11ChannelAgilityEnabled
dot11ChannelAgilityEnabled.description: This attribute indicates that the PHY channel agility functionality is enabled.

dot11HRCCAModeSupported.name: dot11HRCCAModeSupported
dot11HRCCAModeSupported.description: dot11HRCCAModeSupported is a bit-significant value, representing all of the CCA modes supported by the PHY. Valid values are: energy detect only (ED_ONLY) = 01, carrier sense only (CS_ONLY) = 02, carrier sense and energy detect (ED_and_CS)= 04 carrier sense with timer (CS_and_Timer)= 08 high rate carrier sense and energy detect (HRCS_and_ED)= 16 or the logical sum of any of these values. In the high rate extension PHY, this attribute shall be used in preference to the dot11CCAModeSupported attribute.

dot11ShortPreambleOptionImplemented.name: dot11ShortPreambleOptionImplemented
dot11ShortPreambleOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the short preamble option as defined in subclause 18.2.2.2 is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11PBCCOptionImplemented.name: dot11PBCCOptionImplemented
dot11PBCCOptionImplemented.description: This attribute, when true, shall indicate that the PBCC modulation option as defined in subclause 18.4.6.6 is implemented. The default value of this attribute shall be false.

dot11Compliance.name: dot11Compliance
dot11Compliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities that implement the IEEE 802.11 MIB.

dot11SMTbase.name: dot11SMTbase
dot11SMTbase.description: The SMT object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11SMTprivacy.name: dot11SMTprivacy
dot11SMTprivacy.description: The SMTPrivacy package is a set of attributes that shall be present if WEP is implemented in the STA.

dot11MACbase.name: dot11MACbase
dot11MACbase.description: The MAC object class provides the necessary support for the access control, generation, and verification of frame check sequences, and proper delivery of valid data to upper layers.

dot11MACStatistics.name: dot11MACStatistics
dot11MACStatistics.description: The MACStatistics package provides extended statistical information on the operation of the MAC. This package is completely optional.

dot11ResourceTypeID.name: dot11ResourceTypeID
dot11ResourceTypeID.description: Attributes used to identify a STA, its manufacturer, and various product names and versions.

dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup
dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup.description: Attributes for Data Rates for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyTxPowerComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyTxPowerComplianceGroup
dot11PhyTxPowerComplianceGroup.description: Attributes for Control and Management of transmit power.

dot11PhyDSSSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the DSSS for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyIRComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyIRComplianceGroup
dot11PhyIRComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the baseband IR for IEEE 802.11.

dot11PhyRegDomainsSupportGroup.description: Attributes that specify the supported Regulation Domains.

dot11PhyAntennasListGroup.description: Attributes that specify the supported Regulation Domains.

dot11PhyRateGroup.name: dot11PhyRateGroup
dot11PhyRateGroup.description: Attributes for Data Rates for IEEE 802.11.

dot11CountersGroup.name: dot11CountersGroup
dot11CountersGroup.description: Attributes from the dot11CountersGroup that are not described in the dot11MACStatistics group. These objects are mandatory.

dot11SMTbase2.name: dot11SMTbase2
dot11SMTbase2.description: The SMTbase2 object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11PhyHRDSSSComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyHRDSSSComplianceGroup
dot11PhyHRDSSSComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the HRDSSS PHY for IEEE 802.11.

dot11SMTbase3.name: dot11SMTbase3
dot11SMTbase3.description: The SMTbase3 object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network, when the STA is capable of multi-domain operation. This object group should be implemented when the multi-domain capability option is implemented.

dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup.name: dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup
dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup.description: The dot11MultiDomainCapabilityGroup object class provides the objects necessary to manage the channels usable by a STA, when the multi-domain capability option is implemented.

dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup2.name: dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup2
dot11PhyFHSSComplianceGroup2.description: Attributes that configure the Frequency Hopping for operation when multi-domain capability option is implemented.

dot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup.name: dot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup
dot11PhyOFDMComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the OFDM for IEEE 802.11.

dot11RSNAadditions.name: dot11RSNAadditions
dot11RSNAadditions.description: This object class provides the objects from the IEEE 802.11 MIB required to manage RSNA functionality. Note that additional objects for managing this functionality are located in the IEEE 802.11 RSN MIB.

dot11SMTbase4.name: dot11SMTbase4
dot11SMTbase4.description: The SMTbase4 object class provides the necessary support at the IEEE STA to manage the processes in the STA so that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11MACbase2.name: dot11MACbase2
dot11MACbase2.description: The MAC object class provides the necessary support for the access control, generation, and verification of frame check sequences (FCSs), and proper delivery of valid data to upper layers.

dot11CountersGroup2.name: dot11CountersGroup2
dot11CountersGroup2.description: Attributes from the dot11CountersGroup that are not described in the dot11MACStatistics group. These objects are mandatory.

dot11Qosadditions.name: dot11Qosadditions
dot11Qosadditions.description: This object class provides the objects from the IEEE 802.11 MIB required to manage QoS functionality.

dot11SMTbase6.name: dot11SMTbase6
dot11SMTbase6.description: The SMTbase6 object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup2.name: dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup2
dot11PhyAntennaComplianceGroup2.description: Attributes for Data Rates for IEEE 802.11.

dot11MACbase3.name: dot11MACbase3
dot11MACbase3.description: The MAC object class provides the necessary support for the access control, generation, and verification of frame check sequences (FCSs), and proper delivery of valid data to upper layers.

dot11CountersGroup3.name: dot11CountersGroup3
dot11CountersGroup3.description: Attributes from the dot11CountersGroup that are not described in the dot11MACStatistics group. These objects are mandatory.

dot11SMTbase9.name: dot11SMTbase9
dot11SMTbase9.description: The SMTbase9 object class provides the necessary support at the STA to manage the processes in the STA such that the STA may work cooperatively as a part of an IEEE 802.11 network.

dot11PhyMCSGroup.name: dot11PhyMCSGroup
dot11PhyMCSGroup.description: Attributes for Modulation and Coding Schemes (MCS) for IEEE 802.11 HT.

dot1PhyHTComplianceGroup.name: dot1PhyHTComplianceGroup
dot1PhyHTComplianceGroup.description: Attributes that configure the HT for IEEE 802.11.

dot11HTMACAdditions.name: dot11HTMACAdditions
dot11HTMACAdditions.description: Attributes that configure the HT for IEEE 802.11.

dot11TxBFGroup.name: dot11TxBFGroup
dot11TxBFGroup.description: Attributes that configure the Beamforming for IEEE 802.11 HT.

dot11RSNAConfigTable.name: dot11RSNAConfigTable
dot11RSNAConfigTable.description: The table containing RSNA configuration objects.

dot11RSNAConfigVersion.name: dot11RSNAConfigVersion
dot11RSNAConfigVersion.description: The highest RSNA version this entity supports. See 7.3.2.9.

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseKeysSupported.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseKeysSupported
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseKeysSupported.description: This object indicates how many pairwise keys the entity supports for RSNA.

dot11RSNAConfigGroupCipher.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupCipher
dot11RSNAConfigGroupCipher.description: This object indicates the group cipher suite selector the entity must use. The group cipher suite in the RSN Information Element shall take its value from this variable. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyMethod.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyMethod
dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyMethod.description: This object selects a mechanism for rekeying the RSNA GTK. The default is time-based, once per day. Rekeying the GTK is only applicable to an entity acting in the Authenticator role (an AP in an ESS).

dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyTime.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyTime
dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyTime.description: The time in seconds after which the RSNA GTK shall be refreshed. The timer shall start at the moment the GTK was set using the MLMESETKEYS. request primitive.

dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyPackets.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyPackets
dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyPackets.description: A packet count (in 1000s of packets) after which the RSNA GTK shall be refreshed. The packet counter shall start at the moment the GTK was set using the MLME-SETKEYS.request primitive and it shall count all packets encrypted using the current GTK.

dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyStrict.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyStrict
dot11RSNAConfigGroupRekeyStrict.description: This object signals that the GTK shall be refreshed whenever a STA leaves the BSS that possesses the GTK.

dot11RSNAConfigPSKValue.name: dot11RSNAConfigPSKValue
dot11RSNAConfigPSKValue.description: The PSK for when RSNA in PSK mode is the selected AKM suite. In that case, the PMK will obtain its value from this object. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

dot11RSNAConfigPSKPassPhrase.name: dot11RSNAConfigPSKPassPhrase
dot11RSNAConfigPSKPassPhrase.description: The PSK, for when RSNA in PSK mode is the selected AKM suite, is configured by dot11RSNAConfigPSKValue. An alternative manner of setting the PSK uses the password-to-key algorithm defined in H.4. This variable provides a means to enter a pass-phrase. When this object is written, the RSNA entity shall use the password-to-key algorithm specified in H.4 to derive a preshared and populate dot11RSNAConfigPSKValue with this key. This object is logically write-only. Reading this variable shall return unsuccessful status or null or zero.

dot11RSNAConfigGroupUpdateCount.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupUpdateCount
dot11RSNAConfigGroupUpdateCount.description: The number of times Message 1 in the RSNA Group Key Handshake will be retried per GTK Handshake attempt.

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseUpdateCount.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseUpdateCount
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseUpdateCount.description: The number of times Message 1 and Message 3 in the RSNA 4-Way Handshake will be retried per 4-Way Handshake attempt.

dot11RSNAConfigGroupCipherSize.name: dot11RSNAConfigGroupCipherSize
dot11RSNAConfigGroupCipherSize.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the group cipher key.

dot11RSNAConfigPMKLifetime.name: dot11RSNAConfigPMKLifetime
dot11RSNAConfigPMKLifetime.description: The maximum lifetime of a PMK in the PMK cache.

dot11RSNAConfigPMKReauthThreshold.name: dot11RSNAConfigPMKReauthThreshold
dot11RSNAConfigPMKReauthThreshold.description: The percentage of the PMK lifetime that should expire before an IEEE 802.1X reauthentication occurs.

dot11RSNAConfigNumberOfPTKSAReplayCounte.name: dot11RSNAConfigNumberOfPTKSAReplayCounters
dot11RSNAConfigNumberOfPTKSAReplayCounte.description: Specifies the number of PTKSA replay counters per association: 0 -> 1 replay counter, 1 -> 2 replay counters, 2 -> 4 replay counters, 3 -> 16 replay counters

dot11RSNAConfigSATimeout.name: dot11RSNAConfigSATimeout
dot11RSNAConfigSATimeout.description: The maximum time a security association shall take to set up.

dot11RSNAAuthenticationSuiteSelected.name: dot11RSNAAuthenticationSuiteSelected
dot11RSNAAuthenticationSuiteSelected.description: The selector of the last AKM suite negotiated.

dot11RSNAPairwiseCipherSelected.name: dot11RSNAPairwiseCipherSelected
dot11RSNAPairwiseCipherSelected.description: The selector of the last pairwise cipher negotiated.

dot11RSNAGroupCipherSelected.name: dot11RSNAGroupCipherSelected
dot11RSNAGroupCipherSelected.description: The selector of the last group cipher negotiated.

dot11RSNAPMKIDUsed.name: dot11RSNAPMKIDUsed
dot11RSNAPMKIDUsed.description: The selector of the last PMKID used in the last 4-Way Handshake.

dot11RSNAAuthenticationSuiteRequested.name: dot11RSNAAuthenticationSuiteRequested
dot11RSNAAuthenticationSuiteRequested.description: The selector of the last AKM suite requested.

dot11RSNAPairwiseCipherRequested.name: dot11RSNAPairwiseCipherRequested
dot11RSNAPairwiseCipherRequested.description: The selector of the last pairwise cipher requested.

dot11RSNAGroupCipherRequested.name: dot11RSNAGroupCipherRequested
dot11RSNAGroupCipherRequested.description: The selector of the last group cipher requested.

dot11RSNATKIPCounterMeasuresInvoked.name: dot11RSNATKIPCounterMeasuresInvoked
dot11RSNATKIPCounterMeasuresInvoked.description: Counts the number of times that a TKIP MIC failure occurred two times within 60 s and TKIP countermeasures were invoked. This attribute counts both local and remote MIC failure events reported to this STA. It increments every time TKIP countermeasures are invoked

dot11RSNA4WayHandshakeFailures.name: dot11RSNA4WayHandshakeFailures
dot11RSNA4WayHandshakeFailures.description: Counts the number of 4-Way Handshake failures.

dot11RSNAConfigNumberOfGTKSAReplayCounte.name: dot11RSNAConfigNumberOfGTKSAReplayCounters
dot11RSNAConfigNumberOfGTKSAReplayCounte.description: Specifies the number of GTKSA replay counters per association: 0 -> 1 replay counter, 1 -> 2 replay counters, 2 -> 4 replay counters, 3 -> 16 replay counters

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersTable.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersTable
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersTable.description: This table lists the pairwise ciphers supported by this entity. It allows enabling and disabling of each pairwise cipher by network management. The pairwise cipher suite list in the RSN Information Element is formed using the information in this table.

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersEntry.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersEntry
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersEntry.description: The table entry, indexed by the interface index (or all interfaces) and the pairwise cipher.

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherIndex.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherIndex
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherIndex.description: The auxiliary index into the dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCiphersTable.

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipher.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipher
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipher.description: The selector of a supported pairwise cipher. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherEnabled.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherEnabled
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherEnabled.description: This object enables or disables the pairwise cipher.

dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherSize.name: dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherSize
dot11RSNAConfigPairwiseCipherSize.description: This object indicates the length in bits of the pairwise cipher key. This should be 256 for TKIP and 128 for CCMP.

dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuitesTable.name: dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuitesTable
dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuitesTable.description: This table lists the AKM suites supported by this entity. Each AKM suite can be individually enabled and disabled. The AKM suite list in the RSN information element is formed using the information in this table.

dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuiteIndex.name: dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuiteIndex
dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuiteIndex.description: The auxiliary variable used as an index into the dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuitesTable.

dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuite.name: dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuite
dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuite.description: The selector of an AKM suite. It consists of an OUI (the first 3 octets) and a cipher suite identifier (the last octet).

dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnable.name: dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnabled
dot11RSNAConfigAuthenticationSuiteEnable.description: This variable indicates whether the corresponding AKM suite is enabled/disabled.

dot11RSNAStatsTable.name: dot11RSNAStatsTable
dot11RSNAStatsTable.description: This table maintains per-STA statistics in an RSN. The entry with dot11RSNAStatsSTAAddress set to FF-FF-FF-FF-FF-FF shall contain statistics for broadcast/multicast traffic.

dot11RSNAStatsIndex.name: dot11RSNAStatsIndex
dot11RSNAStatsIndex.description: An auxiliary index into the dot11RSNAStatsTable.

dot11RSNAStatsSTAAddress.name: dot11RSNAStatsSTAAddress
dot11RSNAStatsSTAAddress.description: The MAC address of the STA to which the statistics in this conceptual row belong.

dot11RSNAStatsVersion.name: dot11RSNAStatsVersion
dot11RSNAStatsVersion.description: The RSNA version with which the STA associated.

dot11RSNAStatsSelectedPairwiseCipher.name: dot11RSNAStatsSelectedPairwiseCipher
dot11RSNAStatsSelectedPairwiseCipher.description: The pairwise cipher suite Selector (as defined in 7.3.29.1) used during association, in transmission order.

dot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors.name: dot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors
dot11RSNAStatsTKIPICVErrors.description: Counts the number of TKIP ICV errors encountered when decrypting packets for the STA.

dot11RSNAStatsTKIPLocalMICFailures.name: dot11RSNAStatsTKIPLocalMICFailures
dot11RSNAStatsTKIPLocalMICFailures.description: Counts the number of MIC failures encountered when checking the integrity of packets received from the STA at this entity.

dot11RSNAStatsTKIPRemoteMICFailures.name: dot11RSNAStatsTKIPRemoteMICFailures
dot11RSNAStatsTKIPRemoteMICFailures.description: Counts the number of MIC failures encountered by the STA identified by dot11StatsSTAAddress and reported back to this entity.

dot11RSNAStatsCCMPReplays.name: dot11RSNAStatsCCMPReplays
dot11RSNAStatsCCMPReplays.description: The number of received CCMP MPDUs discarded by the replay mechanism.

dot11RSNAStatsCCMPDecryptErrors.name: dot11RSNAStatsCCMPDecryptErrors
dot11RSNAStatsCCMPDecryptErrors.description: The number of received MPDUs discarded by the CCMP decryption algorithm.

dot11RSNAStatsTKIPReplays.name: dot11RSNAStatsTKIPReplays
dot11RSNAStatsTKIPReplays.description: Counts the number of TKIP replay errors detected.

dot11HTOperationalMCSSet.name: dot11HTOperationalMCSSet
dot11HTOperationalMCSSet.description: This attribute shall specify the set of MCS at which the station may transmit data. Each octet contains a value representing a rate. Each MCS shall be within the range from 1 to 127, and shall be supported for receiving data. This value is reported in transmitted Beacon, Probe Request, Probe Response, Association Request, Association Response, Reassociation Request, and Reassociation Response frames, and is used to determine whether a BSS with which the station desires to synchronize is suitable. It is also used when starting a BSS, as specified in 10.3.

dot11MinimumMPDUStartSpacing.name: dot11MinimumMPDUStartSpacing
dot11MinimumMPDUStartSpacing.description: This attribute indicates the minimum time between the start of adjacent MPDUs within an A-MPDU. This time is measured at the PHY-SAP; the number of octets between the start of two consecutive MPDUs in A-MPDU shall be equal or greater than (dot11MinimumMPDUStartSpacing*PHY-bit-rate)/8. The encoding of the minimum time to this attribute is: 0 no restriction 1 1/4 microsec 2 1/2 microsec 3 1 microsec 4 2 microsec 5 4 microsec 6 8 microsec 7 16 microsec The default value of this attribute is 0.
